# Plaintext Firebase config — keep local (the committed .enc.js is the source of truth)
firebase-config.local.json

# NOTE: firebase-key.local.js IS committed on purpose. A Firebase *web* config is an
# identifier, not a secret; the public site must be able to decrypt firebase-config.enc.js
# to talk to Firebase. Real protection = Authorized domains + Security Rules + App Check.
# (Same decision as the AI_BOOK sibling project.)

